Your package python3-cherrypy failed to build from source in current rawhide.
http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=12863540
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_24_Mass_Rebuild

This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 24 development cycle. Changing version to '24'.
More information and reason for this action is here: https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_Program_Management/HouseKeeping/Fedora24#Rawhide_Rebase

The first error thrown out during the mock build:
"ERROR: test suite for <class 'cherrypy.test.test_config.ConfigTests'>" "AttributeError', ("'Call' object has no attribute 'starargs'",)"
appears to be an upstream issue related to changed API in Python3.5:
https://bitbucket.org/cherrypy/cherrypy/issues/1382/configuration-error-with-python-35

Another build failure issue is how python 3.5 handles test discovery. By adding a BuildRequires for python3-mock, and using patch provided by T. Orsava in [0] only one error remains to be handled for which there is already an issue reported at[1].
[0] https://bitbucket.org/cherrypy/cherrypy/issues/1382/configuration-error-with-python-35
[1] https://bitbucket.org/cherrypy/cherrypy/issues/1406/test_2_keyboardinterrupt-failing-on-python
